node.text:
Hi! This is @katyzientek.tinyliving and I'm taking over @tinyhouse IG today answering questions in the comments below about my tiny house 👇🏼

Welcome to my 280 SQ ft tiny home that I share with my husband and our two kids!
We are located in Fayetteville, Texas! Close to the famous Round Top, Texas.
We started remodeling an old shed that's on our property in September 2020, and finished in May 2021. My husband and I did most of the work, but we had some help along the way from family and friends!
The main reason we went tiny is to save money and live rent free....and also because I love tiny homes so much!

If you head over to my IG you can see my "tiny house remodel" highlights from when we started this project to now! 

A few details about our tiny home:

•The tiny house was once a shed that my husband's grandparents would use for storage.

•It's located on the same property as our "forever home" that we plan to remodel...soon! 

•The tiny house is 280 SQ foot (14x20) with an added porch.

Any questions about the tiny house or living tiny?!
Ask below ⏬⏬

I will be answering them from my account in the comments down below!

Photos + home by @katyzientek.tinyliving

good architecture + getaway vibes 💤 
to post a good lookin’ home that soothes the eye & makes us want to escape our present reality like a shot of heroin is useless when current, worthwhile issues aren’t given attention. with that said, let’s take a minute to ween ourselves from tiny house/design porn & direct our attention + thoughts to Afghanistan. lots of folks that are gonna be affected thru this. 🙌🏽 
we don’t grow faint hearted, for we know Where our hope lies.

node.text:
Kylie-Ann’s (@i.built.a.glampervan) van conversion out of Australia is a stunner. 🇦🇺
Earlier this year, she remolded it. First 3 photos are after the remodel, all the rest are from before. 🙌🏼

Some features:

- a bushman 130Ltr 12 volt fridge
- 2 burner gas cooktop
- Dometic cts4110 toilet with a removable cassette 

Get out there & take action with your dream! 👊🏼 you’ve got a community behind you supporting you. Let’s look at alternative ways to live with the climate of unrest happening in the world! 

Photos + home by @i.built.a.glampervan
